BASH - new commands 

pwdx - print process working directory
	pwdx 3315
	3511: /home/cvetomir

lsof -i - a utility that displays information about open file descriptors
	- print open files and processes that use them 

	lsof -i 
	lsof -i :3315 - print ports and processes that use them 
netstat - a tool used to get information about the network state
	netstat -tulnp - lists open network ports and the processes
			that own them

chkconfig -  it is  used  to  manipulate the runlevel links at boot time

route - show / manipulate the IP routing table
	route -n
	/proc/net/route

iostat - display statistics about the hard disk devices
       
	iostat -dmx

readlink - print value of a symbolic link or canonical file name

service - run a SystemV init script

tasksel - a user interface for installing tasks 

egrep - grep with extended regular expressions support

xargs - allows using the output of one command as arguments to another

id [username] - displays UID, GID, groups

modprobe - add and remove modules from the Linux kernel 

usermod - modify a user account

/etc/network/interface - this file describes the network interfaces on your system

/etc/services - this file describes the default ports for various protocols and services

/etc/hosts
	/etc/init.d/network(ing) restart - it is recommended after editting the hosts file

xargs - used to manage arguments between commands 

pgrep - look up process id based on name

      pgrep -l $process-name - lists process names and ids starting with $process-name

fg - kills stopped processes

