PHP Handlers:
http://chriswiegman.com/2011/10/fastcgi-vs-suphp-vs-cgi-vs-mod_php-dso/

Differences:
	*mod_php (DSO) - Runs PHP as part of Apache. PHP is run directly in the same process as the 
		       	 Apache server. all work on files will be done as the Apache user which therefore
			 must have permissions to all of your files. The Apache user must have 
			 permissions on your files. Often the files on your site are owned by users
			 other than your apache user, therefore it will be hard for other users to
			 upload files.

	*CGI 		- PHP is run as a separate cgi process, in a program outside the apache process
			  Requires more CPU time than mod_php. 

	*suPHP		- Runs PHP outside of the Apache process as the user who owns the files. 

	*FastCGI

	*suexec

Best PHP Security practises:
http://www.cyberciti.biz/tips/php-security-best-practices-tutorial.html

